<br>
I was not in NYC when it happened.  My wife works for a company that had one of it's offices in Tower 2.  She would go down there 1 or two times a month.  Fortunately she was not there that day.  Although it took until the late afternoon to find out that her boss and everyone from her company got out ok.  They were on the 17th floor.<br>
<br>
When we made it down there for the News, we were set up for our live shots in Staton Island, where we all had the very depressing view of New York's new skyline.<br>
<br>
Of course even when we came back, every story we did for awhile had something to do with 9/11.  It was a very difficult time.<br>
<br>
