<br>
I was home sick that day. I logged into work and saw some message about &quot;Due to the events in New York and Washington, the internet is likely to be very slow today&quot; and figured there was some DoS attack or something. Then I saw a message that said &quot;We understand that some of you may feel like you need to be with your families today&quot; and I though - Whoa! Time to go check out a news site! I actually walked to a TV, and the first image I saw was, of course, a billowing pair of twin towers.<br>
<br>
Makes a DoS attack seem pretty inconcequential. Makes the availability of the internet seem pretty inconcequential. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub135.ezboard.com/usingsang.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SingSang</A> at: 10/13/02 10:27:59 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#00000F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub135.ezboard.com/uahnyawizard.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ahnya Wizard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#A8A8A8>(10/13/02 9:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub135.ezboard.com/fexodusfellowshipforumfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   911</span><hr size=1> I was afraid for my mother because I knew that some days she would have 2 go 2 the Pentagon.  She was elsewhere.  I do not know what I would do w/out my mother.  She is like the only family that I have and I would miss her terribly and be filled w/ much grief.<br>
